      <hedline>
        <hl1>Smart Appliances</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter by Dr Nevin Cohen on April 13 article on smart appliances; says use of such devices will help in water and energy conservation</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Smart appliances may not make household chores easier, but they can be enormously beneficial to the environment (''Putting a Chip in Every Pot,'' April 13).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Smart appliances may not make household chores easier, but they can be enormously beneficial to the environment (''Putting a Chip in Every Pot,'' April 13).</p>
        <p>By remotely monitoring and adjusting the electricity consumed by internet-linked heaters, dishwashers and ovens, energy utilities will be able to moderate peaks in consumption.</p>
        <p>Through an Internet connection, manufacturers can offer major appliances like washing machines on a pay-per-use basis, encouraging water and energy conservation.</p>
        <p>NEVIN COHEN, Ph.D.  New York</p>
        <p>The writer is an environmental analyst.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
